# shared/.htpasswd-monitoring.example
# Placeholder for the basic-auth user file mounted into shared-nginx at
# /etc/nginx/.htpasswd-monitoring (gates all /monitoring* routes).
#
# Copy to shared/.htpasswd-monitoring and replace with real entries:
#   cd /opt/shared
#   htpasswd -c .htpasswd-monitoring monitor     # first user (-c CREATES/truncates)
#   htpasswd    .htpasswd-monitoring alice        # more users (NO -c)
#
# Each non-comment line is "user:hashed-password". The line below is the bcrypt
# hash for user "monitor" / password "monitor" — DEMO ONLY, do not deploy as-is.
monitor:$apr1$demoSALT$Q9Yq0pZ3demohashdemohash0
